Sentencas: In the present contribution, we combine modeling and experimental study of electrochemical hydrogen oxidation at an alternative perovskite based mixed-conducting SOFC anode.
Titulo: Towards understanding surface chemistry and electrochemistry of La0.1Sr0.9TiO3-α based solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: Composite electrodes were produced by conventional wet ceramic processing (screen printing - spraying) and sintering on YSZ electrolytes (La0.1Sr0.9TiO3-alpha-Ce1-xGdxO2-alpha vertical bar YSZ) with different compositions and microstructure, and were electrochemically characterized using symmetrical button-cells configuration.
Titulo: Towards understanding surface chemistry and electrochemistry of La0.1Sr0.9TiO3-α based solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: An elementary kinetic model was developed and applied to explore the performance of LST based SOFC anode.
Titulo: Towards understanding surface chemistry and electrochemistry of La0.1Sr0.9TiO3-α based solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: A detailed multi-step heterogeneous chemical and electrochemical reaction mechanism was established taking into account transport of ions in all ionic phases, and gas transport in channel and porous media.
Titulo: Towards understanding surface chemistry and electrochemistry of La0.1Sr0.9TiO3-α based solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: It was found that heterogeneous chemistry at LST surface has capacitive behavior that alters the impedance spectra.
Titulo: Towards understanding surface chemistry and electrochemistry of La0.1Sr0.9TiO3-α based solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: In addition, surface charge-transfer reaction, which describes partial oxygen ionization, caused impedance feature and is rate-limiting at high temperature.
Titulo: Towards understanding surface chemistry and electrochemistry of La0.1Sr0.9TiO3-α based solid oxide fuel cell anodes
